Manchester United's player, Fred, tries to take a corner kick during their Premier League match against Manchester City on Saturday. JPOHANNESBURG - A Manchester City football fan has been arrested for allegedly directing monkey gestures, at Manchester United players Fred and Jesse Lingard. The incident took place during the hotly contested Manchester derby, at the home of the defending champions, City. READ: Man City condemn 'racist gesture' during Manchester derby Police in Greater Manchester have confirmed that Anthony Burke has been detained. The fan has protested his innocence, insisting that he's not racist, and that he was just putting his hands in his pockets. He has since been suspended from his job at a building company, while calls are growing for tougher action to be taken against racist chants. The incident has overshadowed United's 2-1 away win, after City's dominance in recent years.